1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:03,359
The Seller registers a represented receivable.

2
00:00:03,359 --> 00:00:07,916
Open RFQ stays blocked until both attestations exist.

3
00:00:07,916 --> 00:00:12,395
Compliance and Risk then issue separate, scoped attestations.

4
00:00:12,395 --> 00:00:16,497
Compliance records eligibility; Risk records the tier.

5
00:00:16,497 --> 00:00:19,362
Both are now recorded, so the Seller can

6
00:00:19,362 --> 00:00:20,078
open RFQ.

7
00:00:20,078 --> 00:00:23,988
The Seller derives certificates and creates one private

8
00:00:23,988 --> 00:00:26,432
request for each invited Funder.

9
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:30,319
These are real Daml contracts, with role-specific signatories

10
00:00:30,319 --> 00:00:34,206
and observers, while the raw debtor identity remains

11
00:00:34,206 --> 00:00:35,664
with the Seller.
